#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:4
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:6
msgid ""
"This chapter explains how to change Blender's default configuration with "
"the *Preferences* editor."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:8
msgid ""
"The Blender *User Preferences* editor contains settings to control how "
"Blender behaves. At the left of the editor, the available options are "
"grouped into tabs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:13
msgid "Blender Preferences window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:17
msgid "Opening Preferences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:19
msgid ""
"While the *Preferences* is its own editor type the best and easiest way "
"to open it is in a new window. To open the *Preferences* editor go to "
":menuselection:`Edit --> Preferences...`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:24
msgid "Save User Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:26
msgid ""
"Once you have set your preferences, you can either manually save them, or"
" just close the window and they will be saved automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:29
msgid ""
"To manually save the preferences, from the preferences window open the "
"small menu in the bottom left and select *Save Current State*. There are "
"two other options related to saving the preferences:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:33
msgid "Revert to Saved"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:34
msgid ""
"Undoes any unsaved modifications to preferences back to the previous "
"saved state."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:36
msgid "Auto-Save Preferences"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:36
msgid ""
"Toggle whether or not the preferences are saved when exiting the "
"*Preferences* window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:40
msgid ""
"It can be valuable to make a backup of your preferences in the event that"
" you lose your configuration."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:42
msgid ""
"See the :doc:`directory layout "
"</getting_started/installing/configuration/directories>` section to see "
"where your preferences are stored."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:49
msgid "Load Factory Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:51
msgid ""
"If you want to completely undo all the modifications made to the "
"preferences and revert them to the factory settings. Open the menu at the"
" bottom left and select *Load Factory Settings*. Note that no permanent "
"changes are made until you save the preferences or close the preferences "
"window."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:57
msgid ""
"Using this only resets the preferences and will not affect settings "
"stored in the startup file. This includes app templates, area locations, "
"and any Blender properties not part of the preferences."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/preferences/introduction.rst:60
msgid "These must be reverted though :menuselection:`File --> Defaults`."
msgstr ""

